#Text=8. How the Grand Gallipoot Joined The Nomes
#Text=After leaving the Whimsies , Guph continued on his journey and penetrated far into the Northwest .
#Text=He wanted to get to the Country of the Growleywogs , and in order to do that he must cross the Ripple Land , which was a hard thing to do .
#Text=For the Ripple Land was a succession of hills and valleys , all very steep and rocky , and they changed places constantly by rippling .
#Text=While Guph was climbing a hill it sank down under him and became a valley , and while he was descending into a valley it rose up and carried him to the top of a hill .
#Text=This was very perplexing to the traveler , and a stranger might have thought he could never cross the Ripple Land at all .

#Text=But Guph knew that if he kept steadily on he would get to the end at last ; so he paid no attention to the changing hills and valleys and plodded along as calmly as if walking upon the level ground .
#Text=The result of this wise persistence was that the General finally reached firmer soil and , after penetrating a dense forest , came to the Dominion of the Growleywogs .

#Text=No sooner had he crossed the border of this domain when two guards seized him and carried him before the Grand Gallipoot of the Growleywogs , who scowled upon him ferociously and asked him why he dared intrude upon his territory .
#Text=" I 'm the Lord High General of the Invincible Army of the Nomes , and my name is Guph , " was the reply .

column1: #Text=" All the world trembles when that name is mentioned . "
#Text=The Growleywogs gave a shout of jeering laughter at this , and one of them caught the Nome in his strong arms and tossed him high into the air .
#Text=Guph was considerably shaken when he fell upon the hard ground , but he appeared to take no notice of the impertinence and composed himself to speak again to the Grand Gallipoot .
#Text=" My master , King Roquat the Red , has sent me here to confer with you .
#Text=The voice of the Grand Gallipoot was partly a roar and partly a growl .
#Text=He mumbled his words badly and Guph had to listen carefully in order to understand him .
#Text=These Growleywogs were certainly remarkable creatures .
#Text=They were of gigantic size , yet were all bone and skin and muscle , there being no meat or fat upon their bodies at all .
#Text=Their powerful muscles lay just underneath their skins , like bunches of tough rope , and the weakest Growleywog was so strong that he could pick up an elephant and toss it seven miles away .
#Text=It seems unfortunate that strong people are usually so disagreeable and overbearing that no one cares for them .
#Text=In fact , to be different from your fellow creatures is always a misfortune .
#Text=The Growleywogs knew that they were disliked and avoided by every one , so they had become surly and unsociable even among themselves .
#Text=Guph knew that they hated all people , including the Nomes ; but he hoped to win them over , nevertheless , and knew that if he succeeded they would afford him very powerful assistance .
#Text="

#Text= Her people are all happy and contented and have no care or worries whatever . "

column1: #Text=" Go on ! " growled the Grand Gallipoot .
#Text=" Once the Nome King enslaved the Royal Family of Ev -- another goody-goody lot that we detest , " said the General .
#Text=" But Ozma interfered , although it was none of her business , and marched her army against us .
#Text=Guph tried to think what to say next , and a happy thought soon occurred to him .
#Text=" We want you to help us in this conquest , " he announced , " for we need the mighty aid of the Growleywogs in order to make sure that we shall not be defeated .

#Text=I am sure it will be a real pleasure to you to tear down the beautiful Emerald City , and in return for your valuable assistance we will allow you to bring back to your country ten thousand people of Oz , to be your slaves .

_	_	_	_

#Text= Twenty thousand ! " growled the Grand Gallipoot .

column1: #Text=" All right , we promise you twenty thousand , " agreed the General .

#Text=The Gallipoot made a signal and at once his attendants picked up General Guph and carried him away to a prison , where the jailer amused himself by sticking pins in the round fat body of the old Nome , to see him jump and hear him yell .
